===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|sleep|lang=enm}}, {{term|sleepe|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|sc=Latinx|slǣp||sleep}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*slēpaz||sleep}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*(s)lāb-||to hang loosely, be limp, be languid}}. Cognate with {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|sliep||sleep|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|stq|-}} {{term|Släip||sleep|lang=stq}}, {{etyl|nds|-}} {{term|Slaap||sleep|lang=nds}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|slaap||sleep|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Schlaf||sleep|lang=de}}, {{etyl|ru|-}} {{term|сла́бый||weak|lang=ru}}.

The verb is from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|slepen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|sc=Latinx|slǣpan||to sleep}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*slēpaną||to sleep}}, from the same root as the noun.

